You are working on ECL-Server, a FastAPI backend for an IFRS 9 Expected Credit Loss (ECL) SaaS platform.

CODEBASE RULES — MANDATORY:

1. NEVER touch the ECL-Web directory. Read it only for type contracts.
2. Every new module follows the exact pattern in app/modules/segments/ — this is the canonical pattern.
3. All DB IDs are ULID strings: String(26). Import new_ulid from app/core/utils.
4. All models use SQLAlchemy 2.0 Mapped[type] + mapped_column() syntax — no old Column() syntax.
5. Services are async. Use AsyncSession. NEVER call db.commit() in services — only db.flush(). The router/dependency layer commits.
6. Errors use ECLException from app/core/exceptions. Never raise raw HTTPException.
7. All responses use the Response(data=...) envelope wrapper. Never return raw dicts.
8. Soft deletes use deleted_at timestamp. Never hard delete business data.
9. Every query on tenant-scoped data MUST include tenant_id in the WHERE clause.
10. git add with specific file paths only. Never git add . or git add -A.
11. Never git push. Only git add + git commit after each completed task.
12. Run ruff check app/ and mypy app/ before committing.

TECH STACK:
- FastAPI 0.100+, SQLAlchemy 2.0+, Alembic, PostgreSQL
- Celery + Redis (db0=cache, db1=celery)
- MinIO / S3 via aiobotocore
- JWT RS256 auth, Argon2 passwords, ULID IDs
- Pydantic v2 schemas

CANONICAL PATTERN FILES — read these first when building any new module:
- Models:    app/modules/segments/models.py
- Service:   app/modules/segments/service.py
- Router:    app/modules/segments/router.py
- Schemas:   app/modules/segments/schemas.py
- Paginator: app/core/pagination.py
- Errors:    app/core/exceptions.py
- Deps:      app/dependencies.py
